Subject: CLAIMS C9030604 -Fire at 23 Mays Street Devonport 2026-001966

Hi Abi,

Further to Wynn Williams letter to Tower dated 3 March 2026 and our discuss=
ion today I confirm our discussion as follows:

This matter has been transferred to me today as my colleague Arna is on fam=
ily leave and is no longer dealing with claims.

Tower is concerned that this matter may stagnate and the parties need to re=
ach a go forward position so that the house can be repaired.

Tower will request ASURNZ to provide a response to the Prendos report detai=
ling why they don=E2=80=99t believe a Building Consent is necessary.

Tower believes the scope of works is appropriate and accordingly if your cl=
ient doesn=E2=80=99t believe this to be the case we invite her to provide a=
 response on the ASURNZ scope of works detailing in the scope of works wher=
e she doesn=E2=80=99t agree and adding any further items she thinks should =
be included. It is not Tower=E2=80=99s practice to pay for the costs of an =
Insured=E2=80=99s alternate scope of works as usually these are agreed betw=
een the parties through discussion.

Tower would like to know your client=E2=80=99s preference regarding cash se=
ttlement or Tower managed repair, noting that ultimately Tower has final di=
scretion as to which option is taken.

We look forward to your further response and receipt of a marked-up scope o=
f works.

Kind Regards




[cid:image001.jpg@01DCD711.4FC61630]
Rachael Keenan
Senior Corporate Counsel
