<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white">Good afternoon Rachael, Thank you for your emai=
l. We share your concern that this matter is stagnating. However, from our =
client=E2=80=99s point of view, that is because
 Tower has scoped works which expressly require Building Consent, but with =
no allowance<o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Good aftern=
oon Rachael,
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Thank you f=
or your email.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">We share yo=
ur concern that this matter is stagnating. However, from our client=E2=80=
=99s point of view, that is because Tower has scoped works
 which expressly require Building Consent, but with no allowance for consen=
t work.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">The positio=
n you express in your email below is simply repeating the view in Lance=E2=
=80=99s email from 27 March. That is: Tower says that the
 repair work scoped does not require building consent because Tower says it=
 does not require building consent. You have provided no expert opinion on =
this other than saying =E2=80=9CTower believes the scope of works is approp=
riate=E2=80=9D. You have not even provided a reasoned
 statement of why Tower says Prendos is wrong, with specific reference to t=
he Building Act.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Our client =
has already paid for Prendos to assess ASURNZ=E2=80=99s repair scope, and h=
as provided Prendo=E2=80=99s expert comments on ASURNZ=E2=80=99s scope,
 which Tower has not engaged with.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">We do not t=
hink that the logical next step is for Tower to put its insured to more cos=
t by requiring her to pay for an alternative repair
 scope which Tower will then ignore, like it is ignoring Prendos=E2=80=99 r=
eport. You say that =E2=80=9Cusually scopes of works are agreed between the=
 parties through discussion=E2=80=9D. We agree. That is why we have attempt=
ed to engage with Tower=E2=80=99s scope, and have sought expert
 advice on it which we have shared with Tower. We are attempting to enter a=
 dialogue over scope. It is not our client who is not engaging in discussio=
n. On that basis, we look forward to seeing ASURNZ=E2=80=99s response on th=
e Prendos report. If that can be accepted,
 then we can move on.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">We share a =
common interest in this matter being dealt with quickly. However, that does=
 not mean that our client must simply ignore her
 experts and agree 100% with Tower=E2=80=99s unevidenced beliefs about the =
scope. <o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Our client =
can=E2=80=99t give a preference over cash settlement or Tower managed repai=
r without knowing what work Tower would undertake. Our client
 will only be able to express a preference once she knows what scope Tower =
would undertake or pay for =E2=80=93 it is not fair to pressure her for a p=
reference whilst simultaneously acknowledging that the parties disagree abo=
ut scope. Our client=E2=80=99s preference at this
 point is that Tower works with her to prepare a scope of works which ensur=
es the repairs will meet the Building Code.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Kind regard=
s<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
